title: Queen
overview: A Delhi girl from a traditional family sets out on a solo honeymoon after her marriage gets cancelled.

title: Almost Famous
overview: A high-school boy is given the chance to write a story for Rolling Stone Magazine about an up-and-coming rock band as he accompanies them on their concert tour.

title: Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas
overview: An oddball journalist and his psychopathic lawyer travel to Las Vegas for a series of psychedelic escapades.
stars: ['Johnny Depp', 'Benicio Del Toro', 'Tobey Maguire', 'Michael Lee Gogin']

title: Hunt for the Wilderpeople
overview: A national manhunt is ordered for a rebellious kid and his foster uncle who go missing in the wild New Zealand bush.

title: Interstate 60: Episodes of the Road
overview: Neal Oliver, a very confused young man and an artist, takes a journey of a lifetime on a highway I60 that doesn't exist on any of the maps, going to the places he never even heard of, searching for an answer and his dreamgirl.

title: Fitzcarraldo
overview: The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.

title: The Gold Rush
overview: A prospector goes to the Klondike in search of gold and finds it and more.

title: The Peanut Butter Falcon
overview: Zak runs away from his care home to make his dream of becoming a wrestler come true.

title: Zombieland
overview: A shy student trying to reach his family in Ohio, a gun-toting tough guy trying to find the last Twinkie, and a pair of sisters trying to get to an amusement park join forces to travel across a zombie-filled America.

title: Spartacus
overview: The slave Spartacus leads a violent revolt against the decadent Roman Republic.

title: Inglourious Basterds
overview: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

title: Green Book
overview: A working-class Italian-American bouncer becomes the driver of an African-American classical pianist on a tour of venues through the 1960s American South.

title: Dead Man
overview: On the run after murdering a man, accountant William Blake encounters a strange aboriginal American man named Nobody who prepares him for his journey into the spiritual world.

title: Barry Lyndon
overview: An Irish rogue wins the heart of a rich widow and assumes her dead husband's aristocratic position in 18th-century England.

title: Ed Wood
overview: Ambitious but troubled movie director Edward D. Wood Jr. tries his best to fulfill his dreams, despite his lack of talent.

title: Les triplettes de Belleville
overview: When her grandson is kidnapped during the Tour de France, Madame Souza and her beloved pooch Bruno team up with the Belleville Sisters--an aged song-and-dance team from the days of Fred Astaire--to rescue him.

title: Deliverance
overview: Intent on seeing the Cahulawassee River before it's dammed and turned into a lake, outdoor fanatic Lewis Medlock takes his friends on a canoeing trip they'll never forget into the dangerous American back-country.

title: Togo
overview: The story of Togo, the sled dog who led the 1925 serum run yet was considered by most to be too small and weak to lead such an intense race.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
overview: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

title: G.O.R.A.
overview: A slick young Turk kidnapped by extraterrestrials shows his great « humanitarian spirit » by outwitting the evil commander-in-chief of the planet of G.O.R.A.
